TY  - JOUR
AU  - Flynn, Sean J, Jr.
AU  - Ghent, Andra C
AU  - Tchistyi, Alexei
T1  - Informational Efficiency in Securitization after Dodd-Frank
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa003
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 33
IS  - 11
SP  - 5131
EP  - 5172
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We analyze how Dodd-Frank-mandated risk retention affects the information investors extract from issuers’ retention choices in the CMBS market. We show that the required retention level is both binding and stringent. Although this implies issuers cannot signal using the level of retention, we provide a model showing that signaling can occur by varying the retention structure. The model is consistent with spreads being empirically lower in deals with a purely first-loss retention structure. A stated concern of rulemakers is asymmetric information. However, we show that, post-crisis, the level of asymmetric information in this market is quite low.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa003
ER  - 



